pages.text:
The if statement is used for conditional execution of code blocks. It allows the program to make decisions based on certain conditions.

In Wenyan, the syntax for an if statement is as follows:

```
若 (condition) {
    // code to execute if condition is true
} 否则若 (another_condition) {
    // code to execute if another_condition is true
} 否则 {
    // code to execute if none of the above conditions are true
}
```

Here, `若` means 'if', `否则若` means 'else if', and `否则` means 'else'. The conditions are evaluated in order, and the first true condition will execute its corresponding code block. If none of the conditions are true, the code block under `否则` will be executed.
